    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-11-14T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-11-14T19:00:00-05:00" n="753"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d753">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00115 European War 1939/11–1444:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Consul General at Naples</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Brandt</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-11-14T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >November 14, 1944—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>684. Department is informed by War Department that SACMED<note n="88"
                        xml:id="d753fn88">Supreme Allied Commander, Mediterranean Theater
                        (Wilson).</note> has agreed to repatriation of properly documented United
                    Nations nationals in Italy in so far as military circumstances permit. (See Tam
                    348 November 3 to General Wilson from CCS.<note n="89" xml:id="d753fn89"
                        >Combined Chiefs of Staff; copy of telegram not found in Department
                        files.</note>) In considering applications for repatriation of American
                    nationals residing in your district you should give preference to following
                    categories: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Persons who are ill or disabled.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Persons who are aged and infirm.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>Persons whose repatriation would result in the reunion of
                            families.</item>
                        <label>4.</label>
                        <item>Children under 15 years of age.</item>
                        <label>5.</label>
                        <item>Individual cases, the merits of each to be considered separately: <list>
                                <label>
                                    <hi rend="italic">a</hi>.</label>
                                <item>Persons left alone through the death of a near relative
                                    especially when death caused by hostilities.</item>
                                <label>
                                    <hi rend="italic">b</hi>.</label>
                                <item>Persons whose residences have been destroyed through military
                                    action.</item>
                                <label>
                                    <hi rend="italic">c</hi>.</label>
                                <item>Men of military age or others whose repatriation would aid the
                                    Allied war effort.</item>
                                <label>
                                    <hi rend="italic">d</hi>.</label>
                                <item>Women who are married to Italian nationals but have retained
                                    their American nationality.</item>
                            </list>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>Department notes that repatriation of American civilians escaped from enemy
                    territory is covered by final paragraph of October 5 letter from Headquarters
                        NATOUSA.<note n="90" xml:id="d753fn90">Letter from North African Theater of
                        Operations, United States Army, October 5, not found in Department
                        files.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Issuance of passports and other documents will be covered in a separate
                    communication.</p>
                <pb facs="1231" n="1217" xml:id="pg_1217"/>
                <p>American nationals who are presently receiving financial assistance from official
                    funds should be reminded that they are under obligation to accept earliest
                    opportunity for repatriation and that refusal will result in complete
                    curtailment of further assistance.</p>
                <p>Inform Ampolad Rome and Palermo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
